10.1016/j.jhep.2017.11.034

LAYSUMM

TITLE

Planning and prioritizing direct-acting antivirals treatment for HCV patients in countries with limited resources: Lessons from the Egyptian experience

PARAGRAPH

We are presenting the largest national program for HCV treatment in the world.

We clearly demonstrate that hepatitis C can be cured efficiently in large scale real-life programs.

This is a clear statement that global HCV eradication is foreseeable, providing a model for other countries with limited resources and prevalent HCV.

Moreover, the availability of generic products has influenced the success of this program.